vectorData.altText: 15. The ______________ nerve is associated with cutaneous sensation over the medial thigh, as indicated by the letter A.
That's right! The obturator nerve sends sensory fibres to supply the medial thigh, therefore it is responsible for cutaneous sensation at A.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

The obturator nerve innervates most of the muscles of the medial compartment of the thigh, and is therefore responsible for adduction of the hip.
It supplies the medial thigh with sensory fibres.
